page.title: 13BIRDS 2
page.content: Some birds are big and somebirds are small. Some birds feed off worms, nuts, insects and scraps of food which people have put out in nets or on their lawns. Some put bread out for birds in Winter because they can't find any food because of the cold snow. There are a lot of different kinds of birds in our area. The black-bird is one of the most common birds in our area. It is cruel to collect birds eggs. If you are caught stealing a rare birds egg you can be fined up to Â£300, as wild birds are now protected by law. Many summer visitors can be seen, including the swallow, cuckoo and swift.
